quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,69,"Did you not see those who dispute concerning Allah's Signs? Whence are they, then, being turned astray"
  40,70,Those who gave the lie to this Book and all the Books which We had sent with Our Messengers shall soon come to know the Truth
  40,71,"when fetters and chains shall be on their necks, and they shall be dragged into"
  40,72,"boiling water, and cast into the Fire"
  40,73,"It will then be said to them: “Where are those whom you"
  40,74,"associated with Allah in His Divinity?” They will say: “We have lost them; rather, we never used to call upon anyone before.” Thus will Allah cause them to stumble in error"
  40,75,"(They will be told): “This is because while you were on earth you took delight in untruth and exulted in it"
  40,76,Enter Hell now to abide in it. How woeful is the abode of those who wax proud
  40,77,"So be patient, (O Prophet). Surely Allah's promise is true. Whether We show them a part of the woeful consequences against which We warn them (while you are still in their midst) or We recall you (from this world) before that, eventually it is to Us that they shall be brought back"
  40,78,"Indeed We sent many Messengers before you: of them there are some whose account We have narrated to you and there are others whose account We have not narrated to you. It did not lie in any Messenger's power to bring any Sign except with Allah's leave. So when Allah's decree came, the matter was decided with justice, and those steeped in error courted utter loss, then and there"